OL,3,CThe areas of England at risk of
OL,4,Cdrought ` and where hosepipe bans are
OL,5,Cin place
OL,7,FSeveral water companies have already
OL,8,Fintroduced hosepipe bans, with Thames
OL,9,FWater bringing one in for its 10
OL,10,Fmillion customers on Tuesday.
OL,12,FThe company said water use is
OL,13,Fcurrently 10% above normal in the
OL,14,FThames Valley and the Home Counties,
OL,15,Fas well as 7% above normal in London.
OL,17,FCustomers are currently using an extra
OL,18,F100 million litres every day `
OL,19,Fequivalent to adding all the homes in
OL,20,FManchester to the network, the firm
OL,21,Fadded.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
