PN,30708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1784663291
OL,3,CThe areas of England at risk of
OL,4,Cdrought ` and where hosepipe bans are
OL,5,Cin place
OL,7,FThe Environment Agency said six
OL,8,Freservoirs are currently classed as
OL,9,Fhaving "notably low" levels, including
OL,10,FWimbleball in Somerset, Grafham in
OL,11,FCambridgeshire and Hanningfield in
OL,12,FEssex, while Blagdon reservoir in
OL,13,FSomerset is classed as being
OL,14,F"exceptionally low".
OL,16,FMeanwhile, only 13% of rivers are
OL,17,Fclassed at normal levels for this time
OL,18,Fof year, with the Rivers Avon
OL,19,F(Hampshire), Cam, Derwent (Yorkshire),
OL,20,FSwale, Tone, Wye and Yare currently
OL,21,Fseeing exceptionally low levels.
OL,26,@qD@HOUqD@TO]vD@AOUvD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
