CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1784663291
OL,3,CThe areas of England at risk of
OL,4,Cdrought ` and where hosepipe bans are
OL,5,Cin place
OL,7,FHelen Wakeham, chair of the National
OL,8,FDrought Group and director of water at
OL,9,Fthe Environment Agency, said: "All
OL,10,Fsectors are taking action, and we are
OL,11,Fgrateful to the public for following
OL,12,Fthe restrictions, where in place, to
OL,13,Fmake sure there is enough water for
OL,14,Feveryone this summer.
OL,16,F"We want everyone to stay safe and
OL,17,Fhydrated during the hot weather but
OL,18,Fevery drop we can save is a drop more
OL,19,Ffor nature and agriculture."
OL,26,@qD@_OUxD@AOU
